{"sha": "7b3b2f50953c5143d4b14b59d322d8a793f411dd", "node_id": "C_kwDOANBUbNoAKDdiM2IyZjUwOTUzYzUxNDNkNGIxNGI1OWQzMjJkOGE3OTNmNDExZGQ", "commit": {"author": {"name": "Marek Polacek", "email": "polacek@redhat.com", "date": "2022-11-17T16:59:29Z"}, "committer": {"name": "Marek Polacek", "email": "polacek@redhat.com", "date": "2022-11-18T00:15:57Z"}, "message": "c++: constinit on pointer to function [PR104066]\n\n[dcl.constinit]: \"The constinit specifier shall be applied only to\na declaration of a variable with static or thread storage duration.\"\n\nThus, this ought to be OK:\n\n  constinit void (*p)() = nullptr;\n\nbut the error message I introduced when implementing constinit was\nnot looking at funcdecl_p, so the code above was rejected.\n\nFixed thus.  I'm checking constinit_p first because I think that's\nfar more likely to be false than funcdecl_p.\n\n\tPR c++/104066\n\ngcc/cp/ChangeLog:\n\n\t* decl.cc (grokdeclarator): Check funcdecl_p before complaining\n\tabout constinit.\n\ngcc/testsuite/ChangeLog:\n\n\t* g++.dg/cpp2a/constinit18.C: New test.", "tree": {"sha": "e69fd3fbafeda0b36353ca4c7be6aacb80d3cd2e", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/git/trees/e69fd3fbafeda0b36353ca4c7be6aacb80d3cd2e"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/git/commits/7b3b2f50953c5143d4b14b59d322d8a793f411dd", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": false, "reason": "unsigned", "signature": null, "payload": null}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commits/7b3b2f50953c5143d4b14b59d322d8a793f411dd", "html_url": "https://github.com/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commit/7b3b2f50953c5143d4b14b59d322d8a793f411dd", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commits/7b3b2f50953c5143d4b14b59d322d8a793f411dd/comments", "author": {"login": "mpolacek", "id": 10496300, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEwNDk2MzAw", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/10496300?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mpolacek",